        <p class="h2" style="text-align:center;"><strong>Human Trafficking</strong></p><br />
        <p>
            This initial page gives a brief description on what exactly human trafficking is, and how we as a community can help others who may be victims. It is also a useful resource for families of victims, or anyone else that may be searching for information on the topic.<br />

            <strong>Adults:</strong> In the adults page, there will be different types of resources, such as articles, powerpoints, and personal stories. Users can learn how to spot human trafficking, help those that may be victims, and hopefully help prevent it where possible. It is our belief, that providing information on our site will contribute to a better understanding of resources available to victims, their family, and any other concerned individuals associated with this issue.<br />

            <strong>Teens:</strong> This page displays information, such as articles, powerpoints, personal stores, for teens, ideally in middle and high school. They will be a obtain age appropriate resources associated with human trafficking. These resources will help them become more informed on issues associated with human trafficking and show them how to spot potential warning signs of it taking place in the places they live.<br />

            <strong>Youth:</strong> This page displays information for youth, such as informative powerpoints, ideally for students in elementary schools. The main goal here is to provide some basic examples of effective measures to ensure that these children avoid situations where they may be at risk. We want to present this information in a manner that will not be overwhelming or graphic, but also convey that this is a serious issue. The page will also provide additional resources for children that age, and information on who to reach out to if necessary.<br />

            <strong>Teachers:</strong> This page displays information for teacher/instructors. They will be able to retrieve new information from Ferris instructors. Ferris instructors will also be able to upload new information for teachers to keep them updated on any new information regarding Human Trafficking and how prevent it.<br />

            <strong>Statistics:</strong> This statistics page displays quick facts on Human Trafficking. Show us statistics where Human Trafficking is most common. Also, it shows who is most affected by gender and age. There are also various types of Trafficking reported and it shows a percentage of where Human Trafficking is most common.  This information can be retrieved and updated from  _______.<br />

            <strong>Resources:</strong> This page displays additional resources where anyone will be able to retrieve general information on Human Trafficking. Again, ensuring that we are providing as many applicable and useful resources as possible so that people looking for information can find it easily, and quickly.<br />

        </p>
    </div>
</div>
