        <p class="h2" style="text-align:center;"><strong>Cyber Security</strong></p><br />

        <p>
            The Cyber Security pages are meant to educate the users
            on topics relating to cyber security. Our aim to provide as many resources as possible to help all users stay safe while using the internet.<br />

            <strong>Adults:</strong>In the adults page, there will be different types resources, such as articles, powerpoints, personal stories, where parents or any adult can look into how to make sure they are able to mitigate online risks associated with Human Trafficking. This page will also provide information that adults will also be able to use to help those they care about, and make sure they are taking the proper precautions online.<br />

            <strong>Teens:</strong> This page displays information for teens, in middle and high school, where there will be a different types of resources where teens can become aware of Cyber Security techniques and methods. Some teens do not know how important Cyber Security is, so the resources displayed will help them become more informed and show them what they can do ensure their safe online. If they are already taking precautions online, it will provide them a resource to show their friends and peers what they can do to practice online safety measures.<br />

            <strong>Youth:</strong> This page displays information ideally for students in elementary school, as to help them be better informed about cyber security and its importance. It will teach them techniques on how to avoid cyber security threats. Especially given the rate that children are accessing the internet and taking part in online communities, we wish to ensure that children are able to have something to refer to so they can hopefully avoid falling victim to online threats.<br />

            <strong>Teachers:</strong> This page displays information for teachers and instructors that wish to become more involved in actively fighting Human Trafficking. They will be able to retrieve new information regarding topics of Human Trafficking, and stay up to date with current warning signs and threats. Also the professors and students controlling the content will be able to upload information for teachers, to make it easier for teachers that wish to present this information to their students and their families.<br />

            <strong>Law Enforcement:</strong> This page will provide resources for people wishing to learn more about law enforcement’s role in protecting people from Human Trafficking. It will have information on the current efforts being made to crack down on the occurrence of Human Trafficking, and how to potentially contribute to theses efforts. There will also be numbers and contact information for both the law enforcement agencies currently involved in these efforts, and the local law enforcement entities.<br />

            <strong>Resources:</strong> This page displays additional resources where anyone will able to retrieve general information on Cyber Security. Basically, to ensure that anyone in search of pertinent information on topics of Human Trafficking is able to find this information quickly, and easily.<br />
        </p>
